{
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Sympy: Symbolic Computing {#sec-sympy}\n",
        "\n",
        "$~$\n",
        "\n",
        "[![](https://www.sympy.org/static/images/logo.png)](https://docs.sympy.org/latest/index.html)\n",
        "\n",
        "$~$\n",
        "\n",
        "## Importing sympy\n"
      ],
      "id": "c7c31c43"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import sympy\n",
        "from sympy import I, pi, oo\n",
        "sympy.init_printing()\n",
        "\n",
        "from IPython.display import display\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"sympy: \", sympy.__version__)"
      ],
      "id": "b67cf723",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Symbols\n"
      ],
      "id": "1885efaf"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "x = sympy.Symbol('x')\n",
        "print(x.is_real)"
      ],
      "id": "982253ab",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "y = sympy.Symbol('y', real=True)\n",
        "y.is_real"
      ],
      "id": "a12dc5e9",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "z = sympy.Symbol('z', complex=True)\n",
        "z.is_complex"
      ],
      "id": "5b9f6503",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "print(z.is_real)"
      ],
      "id": "cb0e51c0",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n"
      ],
      "id": "482351e6"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "x = sympy.Symbol('x')\n",
        "y = sympy.Symbol('y', positive=True)\n",
        "z = sympy.Symbol('z', negative=True)"
      ],
      "id": "4e68c778",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.sqrt(x**2)"
      ],
      "id": "d90c1baa",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.sqrt(y**2)"
      ],
      "id": "f5814b2b",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.sqrt(z**2)"
      ],
      "id": "4b48a682",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n"
      ],
      "id": "32ec3efd"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "n1 = sympy.Symbol('n')\n",
        "n2 = sympy.Symbol('n', integer=True)\n",
        "n3 = sympy.Symbol('n', odd=True)\n",
        "n4 = sympy.Symbol('n', even=True)"
      ],
      "id": "fea55b65",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.cos(n1*pi)"
      ],
      "id": "bb9a62ed",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.cos(n2*pi)"
      ],
      "id": "d925e9e3",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.cos(n3*pi)"
      ],
      "id": "ac090fc5",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.cos(n4*pi)"
      ],
      "id": "1069a543",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n"
      ],
      "id": "95e823e1"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "a, b, c = sympy.symbols('a, b, c', negative=True)"
      ],
      "id": "02b17fd8",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "d, e, f = sympy.symbols('d, e, f', positive=True)"
      ],
      "id": "75b1f1b6",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Numbers\n",
        "\n",
        "* We cannot directly use the built-in Python objects for integers, `int`, and floating-point numbers, `float`, and so on. Instead, `sympy` provides the classes `sympy.Integer` and `sympy.Float` for representing integers and floating-point numbers within the `sympy` framework\n",
        "\n",
        "* This distinction is important to be aware of when working with `sympy`, but fortunately we rarely\n",
        "need to concern ourselves with creating objects of type `sympy.Integer` and `sympy.Float` to representing\n",
        "specific numbers, $~$since `sympy` automatically promotes Python numbers to instances of these classes when they occur in `sympy` expressions\n"
      ],
      "id": "870c1409"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "i = sympy.Integer(18)\n",
        "type(i)"
      ],
      "id": "1ba719d5",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "i.is_Integer, i.is_real, i.is_odd, i.is_even"
      ],
      "id": "9745c8c8",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "f = sympy.Float(2.3)\n",
        "type(f)"
      ],
      "id": "b5e1338e",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "f.is_Float, f.is_real, f.is_complex"
      ],
      "id": "1b598eea",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n"
      ],
      "id": "6488e993"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "i, f = sympy.sympify(19), sympy.sympify(2.3)\n",
        "type(i), type(f)"
      ],
      "id": "dac18075",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Integer \n",
        "\n",
        "* While the `Symbol` with `integer=True` represents some integer, $\\,$the `Integer` instance represents a\n",
        "specific integer\n",
        "\n",
        "* For both cases, $\\,$the `is_integer` attribute is `True`, $\\,$but there is also an attribute `is_Integer`\n",
        "(note the capital `I`), $\\,$which is only `True` for `Integer` instances\n"
      ],
      "id": "1ca09853"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "n = sympy.Symbol('n', integer=True)\n",
        "n.is_integer, n.is_Integer, n.is_positive, n.is_Symbol"
      ],
      "id": "f33ccafa",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "i = sympy.Integer(19)\n",
        "i.is_integer, i.is_Integer, i.is_positive, i.is_Symbol"
      ],
      "id": "b59ef3c8",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.Integer('19' *20)"
      ],
      "id": "4ece8705",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.Integer('12_345_678'), sympy.Integer(12_345_678)"
      ],
      "id": "9074038e",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# great common division, leat common multiple\n",
        "sympy.igcd(36, 15), sympy.ilcm(7, 34)"
      ],
      "id": "3df0d8b4",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "* Integers in `sympy` are <font color='red'>**arbitrary precision**</font>, $\\,$meaning that they have <font color='blue'>no fixed lower and upper bounds</font>,\n",
        "$\\,$which is the case when representing integers with a specific bit-size, as, for example, in `numpy`\n"
      ],
      "id": "039bac00"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "i = sympy.Integer(19)\n",
        "i**100"
      ],
      "id": "817eb94f",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.factorial(100)"
      ],
      "id": "be3cfb8f",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Float\n",
        "\n",
        "* Like `Integer`, $\\,$`Float` is <font color='red'>**arbitrary precision**</font>, $\\,$in contrast to Python’s built-in `float` type and the `float` types in `numpy`. $\\,$This means that any `Float` can represent a `float` with arbitrary number of decimals\n",
        "\n",
        "* When a `Float` instance is created using its constructor, $\\,$there are two arguments: the first argument is **a Python `float` or a string representing a floating-point number**, and the second (optional) argument is the **precision** (number of significant decimal digits) of the `Float` object\n"
      ],
      "id": "b0dda77e"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# create a string representation with 25 decimals\n",
        "f'{0.3:.25f}'  "
      ],
      "id": "1cff9b2b",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.Float(0.3, 25) "
      ],
      "id": "156f8954",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.Float('0.3', 25)"
      ],
      "id": "4d938c8b",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.Float('123 456 789.123_456', '')"
      ],
      "id": "c4c12c24",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Rational\n"
      ],
      "id": "c60376d1"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "r0 = sympy.Rational(11, 13)\n",
        "r0"
      ],
      "id": "4ec58452",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "r0.p, r0.q"
      ],
      "id": "d98377b9",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "r1 = sympy.Rational(2, 3)\n",
        "r2 = sympy.Rational(4, 5)"
      ],
      "id": "35337033",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "r1 * r2"
      ],
      "id": "9e99bc20",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "r1 / r2"
      ],
      "id": "1128f776",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.Rational(0.2), sympy.Rational('0.2')"
      ],
      "id": "9089c931",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Constants and special symbols\n",
        "\n",
        "$\\displaystyle \\gamma = \\lim_{n \\to \\infty} \\left( \\sum_{k=1}^n \\frac{1}{k} -\\ln n\\right)$\n"
      ],
      "id": "c3654d89"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.pi, sympy.E, sympy.EulerGamma, sympy.I, sympy.oo"
      ],
      "id": "d55883f4",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Functions\n"
      ],
      "id": "008cb3ce"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "x, y, z = sympy.symbols('x, y, z')"
      ],
      "id": "d01a59f6",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "f = sympy.Function('f')\n",
        "type(f)"
      ],
      "id": "0d5babc3",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "f(x)"
      ],
      "id": "96ca1595",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "g = sympy.Function('g')(x, y, z)\n",
        "g"
      ],
      "id": "35838590",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "g.free_symbols"
      ],
      "id": "a6ffb887",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n"
      ],
      "id": "96112f38"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.sin"
      ],
      "id": "c2486d7b",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.sin(x)"
      ],
      "id": "1881c8d4",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.sin(pi *1.5)"
      ],
      "id": "4881b28c",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "n = sympy.Symbol('n', integer=True)\n",
        "sympy.sin(pi * n)"
      ],
      "id": "7f136fc7",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "h = sympy.Lambda(x, x**2)\n",
        "h"
      ],
      "id": "366966e4",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "h(5)"
      ],
      "id": "33fca49d",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "h(1 + x)"
      ],
      "id": "0f820e1c",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Expressions\n"
      ],
      "id": "2bf24e5d"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "x = sympy.Symbol('x')\n",
        "\n",
        "expr = 1 +2*x**2 +3*x**3\n",
        "expr"
      ],
      "id": "6701b028",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "expr.args"
      ],
      "id": "8b2f4def",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "expr.args[2]"
      ],
      "id": "00c33e49",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "expr.args[2].args"
      ],
      "id": "c3b6f703",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "expr.args[2].args[1]"
      ],
